                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/3711a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-11T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 11, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>164. From the Under Secretary. A broadcast this afternoon announced that
                    “President Vargas of Brazil in a public speech has alluded to the European
                    dictatorships in a complimentary manner”. Please telegraph immediately any basis
                    there may be for this report. [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
